# .mailmap
# BLUEPRINT: Composer 2 implements from this structure
# PURPOSE: Normalize git author names and email addresses for `git shortlog`, `git log --use-mailmap`,
#          and contributor statistics. Optional per spec §26.12 item 405.
# SECTIONS:
#   - One entry per line in format: Canonical Name <canonical@email> Commit Name <commit@email>
#   - Or: Canonical Name <canonical@email> <old@email> — to fix just the email
#   - Or: <canonical@email> <old@email> — to fix just the email, keeping the name
# DESIGN DECISIONS:
#   - Populated when contributors use different email addresses across machines/accounts
#   - Useful for bots: map bot commits to a canonical bot identity
#   - Run `git shortlog -s -n` to see current contributor stats; add entries here to fix

# Example entries (remove/replace with actual entries):
# Correct Name <correct@email.com> Old Name <old@email.com>
# Bot Identity <bot@org.com> github-actions[bot] <41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
